===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈkɒm.juˌnɪzm̩/}}

===Etymology===
A calque of the {{etyl|de|en}} word {{term|Kommunismus|lang=de}} (from Marx and Engels's ''[http://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1848/communist-manifesto/index.htm Manifesto of the German Communist Party]''), in turn a calque of the {{etyl|fr|en}} word {{term|communisme|lang=fr}}, which was formed from {{term|commun||common|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|communis|lang=la}}, and the suffix {{term|-isme||-ism|lang=fr}}.

[[Image:Hammer and sickle.svg|thumb|right|120px|The [[red]] flag, particularly when marked with a [[yellow]] [[hammer]] intersecting a yellow [[sickle]], is an [[icon]]ic [[symbol]] of communism.]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any political philosophy or ideology advocating holding the production of resources collectively.
# Any political social system that implements a communist political philosophy.
# The international socialist society where classes and the state no longer exist.

